channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Minnesota lawmaker sounds alarm on Gov Walz's 'radical agenda' ahead of election: 'So heinous'
item.description: Minnesota GOP State Sen. Mark Koran told Fox News Digital that Gov. Walz's track record in the state shows that he will push a "radical" agenda if elected as vice president.

item.title: Report: Trump campaign staffers had 'physical altercation' with Arlington National Cemetery official
item.description: A physical confrontation reportedly took place Monday at Arlington National Cemetery during former President Trump's wreath-laying visit to mark the anniversary of a fatal suicide bombing in Afghanistan.

item.title: Colorado’s Campaign against Christians Continues
item.description: The state will provide preschool education only to children of parents who are happy to subject them to progressive ideology.

item.title: Pastor Twists Himself In Knots To Claim Being Pro-IVF Is Pro-Life
item.description: Our longings, even for good things, are not a license to take matters of life into our own hands — because the result is the transfer of suffering from adult to child.

item.title: Migrant crisis roils Boston area as school stands firm on Dukakis-era residency policy
item.description: Advocacy groups unsuccessfully demanded Saugus school administrators reverse a residency and census policy they claim disadvantages immigrants from making it into schools.

item.title: Biden pushed Gaza pier over warnings it would undercut other aid routes, watchdog says
item.description: President Joe Biden ordered the construction of a temporary pier to deliver humanitarian aid to Gaza earlier this year even as some staffers for the U.S. Agency for International Development expressed concerns that the effort would be difficult to pull off and undercut the effort to persuade Israel to open "more efficient" land crossings to get food into the territory, according to a USAID inspector general report published Tuesday.

item.title: How Kamala Harris’s First Presidential Campaign Unraveled Thanks to Health-Care Policy
item.description: She tried doing a lot of interviews in 2019 — and it ended badly.

item.title: NASA And Boeing’s Failure Is A Shameful Reminder Of What’s At Stake In The Election
item.description: America's space program is no longer a nationalist vanity project but a serious matter of strategic interest.

item.title: Kamala Harris called for removing cops from schools to fight racial 'inequities' in 2019 interview
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris, when she served as a California senator, advocated for the removal of police officers from schools, according to unearthed 2019 footage.

item.title: Tough week for pro-lifers as activists convicted, pregnancy center attacked after DNC
item.description: It was a rough week for pro-life advocates, and that was before another pregnancy resource center was vandalized.

item.title: The Union Pretends a Deep-State Rescue Mission
item.description: Mark Wahlberg’s and Halle Berry’s thriller-romance nods to populism.

item.title: Democrats May Win The 2024 Election By Buying Swing State Votes
item.description: State and U.S. attorneys general must investigate whether it's legal to provide food, beverages, and entertainment to buy swing-state votes.

item.title: Zuckerberg, expressing regrets, admits bowing to Biden administration pressure to remove content
item.description: Mark Zuckerberg, in a letter to House Judiciary Chairman Jim Jordan, has accepted responsibility and expressed regret for caving to pressure from the White House to censor some COVID-19 content.

item.title: Harris, Walz to sit down for first interview on Thursday
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris will sit down with CNN on Thursday in her first major interview since becoming the Democratic Party's nominee, the network announced Tuesday.

item.title: Biden’s Social-Media Censorship Regime
item.description: Mark Zuckerberg confirmed that the administration pressured Facebook into suppressing speech — including jokes — during the pandemic.

item.title: How ‘America’s Worst Court’ Intimidates Elected Officials To Fight Judicial Reform
item.description: The Montana Supreme Court, which has a long history of corruption, has filed 41 dubious ethics charges against the state attorney general just for doing his job.

item.title: Massachusetts GOP demands information on state's $1 billion in 'secret' migrant spending: 'Veil of secrecy'
item.description: Massachusetts Republicans have submitted a formal request regarding the amount of money that taxpayers are spending to house migrants and information into public safety incidents.

item.title: Rep. Jodey Arrington issues reminders on the effects of Bidenomics
item.description: "While the Conference Board's report showed a slight improvement in consumer confidence, overall markets remain weak and Americans are worried about the health of the labor market," House Budget Committee Chairman Jodey Arrington said in a statement shared with Inside the Beltway.

item.title: How Lincoln Can Help Trump
item.description: Trump’s challenge is to force Kamala Harris out of her self-imposed bubble, and he could apply lessons from history to do so.

item.title: Dems Are Fighting To Keep RFK Jr. On Swing State Ballots As Potential Spoiler Against Trump
item.description: The Democrats have tried to keep left-wing third party candidates off the November ballot.
